description:
&lt;h1&gt;NHS Greater Manchester Shared Services (GMSS)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*Please note that this vacancy is for Greater Manchester Shared Services NOT Salford Royal Foundation Trust*&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Referral Coordinator working in a contact centre environment with a mixture of tasks including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;taking inbound telephone calls from patients who want to book medical appointments, blood tests or non-emergency transport&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;quality checking and processing referrals received from GP practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;dealing with GP practice queries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: alternate weeks 08:00 - 16:00/10:00 - 18:00. Monday - Friday&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Relaxed yet hardworking environment. Extremely friendly, welcoming and supportive team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will be home based initially and therefore reliable home broadband is essential. Full training will be provided&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have fantastic customer service skills and a warm empathetic approach to people, we&#39;d love to hear from you. Feel free to call us to find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Vacant Positions are : -&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 1:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 x 30hrs per week over 4 days, on a 12 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 2:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 x 37.5hrs per week, on a 12 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 3:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 x 37.5hrs per week, on a 9 month fixed term contract.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Option 4:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 x 30hrs per week, until 29th June 2021.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please indicate in your application which of the above options you would like to apply for.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any applications that do not contain this information will be unable to be considered for shortlisting.&lt;/p&gt;
